Notes: This column contains free text or string identifiers for measurements, aligning with the datatype and the property 'hasFreeText'.
The 'patient_id' uniquely identifies a patient and is best mapped through the 'hasSubjectPseudoIdentifier' relationship from Measurement to Patient.
Measurement codes are best represented as codes linking to the 'Code' entity, reflecting standardized coding systems.
Quantitative measurement values are best mapped to the 'Quantity' entity, capturing the numeric value and related units.
Measurement units specify the scale of the measurement and are properly linked through the 'hasUnit' property within Quantity.
The date of measurement is best represented as an xsd:dateTime literal, mapped directly via 'hasMeasurementDateTime'.
